ption":"Gonna Want Seconds"},"image":{"@id":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/#\/schema\/logo\/image\/"},"sameAs":["https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/GWShomecooking\/","https:\/\/x.com\/gonnawantsecond","https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/gonna_want_seconds\/","https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\/gonnawantsecond\/","https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/channel\/UCbi4dOOxKIznbbN1gjxH0Qg"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/#\/schema\/person\/714fc26a29010553e095748f166ff7f5","name":"Kathleen","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/cc872ef202735031e0650b36f4c6232cbc8b4ad26f7f2072125aa43db150c9d9?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/cc872ef202735031e0650b36f4c6232cbc8b4ad26f7f2072125aa43db150c9d9?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/cc872ef202735031e0650b36f4c6232cbc8b4ad26f7f2072125aa43db150c9d9?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Kathleen"},"description":"I’m a home cook and my favorite place to be is in my kitchen cooking up a storm. I’m also a wife, mother, Bernese Mountain dog lover, friend, daughter, sister, and reluctant exerciser.","sameAs":["https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/pages\/Gonna-Want-Seconds\/156179717763462","https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/gonna_want_seconds\/","https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\/gonnawantsecond\/"],"url":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/author\/food-admin\/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"One Pot Burrito Bowls","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kathleen"},"description":"This burrito bowl recipe brings the deliciously authentic flavor you’d expect to find in your favorite Mexican restaurant right to your own table!","datePublished":"2024-01-10T01:00:08+00:00","image":["https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-2.jpg","https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-2-500x500.jpg","https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-2-500x375.jpg","https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-2-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["6","6 people"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT45M","totalTime":"PT55M","recipeIngredient":["2-4  tablespoons vegetable oil (divided)","24 ounces ground beef or ground turkey","2 teaspoons salt (divided)","1\/2 teaspoon black pepper","1\/2 cup yellow onion, (chopped)","4 cloves garlic, (Minced)","1 tablespoon chili powder","1 teaspoon ground cumin","1 teaspoon dried oregano","1\/2 teaspoon smoked paprika","1 cup long grain white rice","1 (14.5-ounce) can  diced tomatoes, (drained)","1\/4 teaspoon granulated sugar","1 (15-ounce) can  black beans,  (drained and rinsed)","1 (4-ounce) can  mild diced green chiles, (drained)","1\/2 cup frozen or canned corn, (thawed and drained)","2  1\/2 cups caldo de pollo or chicken stock","1 cup extra sharp cheddar cheese (grated)","1 cup Monterey jack cheese (shredded)","shredded lettuce or shredded cabbage","cheddar cheese,","Monterey jack cheese,  (shredded)","sour cream","medium tomatoes, (diced)","red onions (sliced)","fresh cilantro, (roughly chopped)","avocado, (sliced)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a large, high-sided skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil over medium heat. Add the ground turkey (24 ounces), 1 teaspoon salt, and 1\/2 teaspoon black pepper. Cook just until the turkey is no longer pink. Remove to a plate and set aside.","name":"In a large, high-sided skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil over medium heat. Add the ground turkey (24 ounces), 1 teaspoon salt, and 1\/2 teaspoon black pepper. Cook just until the turkey is no longer pink. Remove to a plate and set aside.","url":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/#wprm-recipe-16068-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In the same skillet, add 1-2 tablespoons of oil and cook the onion (1\/2 cup) and garlic (4 cloves), over medium-low heat, until they&#39;re soft about 6 minutes. ","name":"In the same skillet, add 1-2 tablespoons of oil and cook the onion (1\/2 cup) and garlic (4 cloves), over medium-low heat, until they&#39;re soft about 6 minutes. ","url":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/#wprm-recipe-16068-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder (1 tablespoon), cumin (1 teaspoon), oregano (1 teaspoon), paprika (1\/2 teaspoon), and cook for 1 minute, stirring often so the spices don&#39;t burn. (If the pan is too dry, add a little oil so spices don&#39;t burn.) ","name":"Add 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder (1 tablespoon), cumin (1 teaspoon), oregano (1 teaspoon), paprika (1\/2 teaspoon), and cook for 1 minute, stirring often so the spices don&#39;t burn. (If the pan is too dry, add a little oil so spices don&#39;t burn.) ","url":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/#wprm-recipe-16068-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the rice (1 cup), canned tomatoes (1 can), sugar (1\/4 teaspoon), black beans (1 can), diced chiles (1 can), corn (1\/2 cup), chicken stock (2 1\/2 cups) and browned turkey and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and cover with a tight-fitting lid. Cook on low until the rice is done and cooked through for about 20 to 25 minutes.","name":"Add the rice (1 cup), canned tomatoes (1 can), sugar (1\/4 teaspoon), black beans (1 can), diced chiles (1 can), corn (1\/2 cup), chicken stock (2 1\/2 cups) and browned turkey and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and cover with a tight-fitting lid. Cook on low until the rice is done and cooked through for about 20 to 25 minutes.","url":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/#wprm-recipe-16068-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Turn the cooktop off, top with the shredded cheese (1 cup cheddar + 1 cup Monterey jack cheese), place the lid back on and let sit until the cheese is melted about 5 minutes.","name":"Turn the cooktop off, top with the shredded cheese (1 cup cheddar + 1 cup Monterey jack cheese), place the lid back on and let sit until the cheese is melted about 5 minutes.","url":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/#wprm-recipe-16068-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Top as desired and serve!","name":"Top as desired and serve!","url":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/#wprm-recipe-16068-step-0-5"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["Mexican"],"keywords":"Burrito Bowl, Mexica Dish, Mexica Dish, Tex Mex","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 \/6 of the recipe","calories":"573 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"50 g","proteinContent":"46 g","fatContent":"21 g","saturatedFatContent":"12 g","cholesterolContent":"102 mg","sodiumContent":"1449 mg","fiberContent":"6 g","sugarContent":"6.5 g"},"@id":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\/\/www.gonnawantseconds.com\/one-pot-burrito-bowl-recipe\/"}]}</script>
