<div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-snippet wprm-recipe-template-linds-buttons"><!-- [wprm-recipe-jump style="button" border_radius="0px" text="JUMP TO RECIPE" font-family= "Rubik" font-weight= "600" font-size= "12px" background= "#464546" color= "#fff" border= "0px"]
[wprm-recipe-rating icon_color="#f8e71c" voteable="1"] --></div><p style="text-align: left;">This post may contain affiliate links. Please read our <a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/disclosure/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>disclosure policy</strong></a>.</p>
<p data-start="717" data-end="1006"><strong data-start="45" data-end="69">One Pot Burrito Bowl</strong> gives you all the bold Tex-Mex flavor of a loaded burrito bowl — seasoned meat, rice, beans, cheese, and toppings — without cooking everything separately. It all comes together in one skillet for an easy, family-friendly dinner with fewer dishes and no complicated steps.</p>
<p data-start="1008" data-end="1229">This recipe is perfect for busy weeknights, meal prep, or feeding a hungry family. Everything cooks together, so the rice soaks up all that savory, spiced flavor, and the result is hearty, satisfying, and incredibly easy.</p>
<p data-start="1231" data-end="1378">If you enjoy easy Tex-Mex dinners like my <strong><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/taco-meat-recipe/">taco meat</a>, <a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/easy-turkey-tacos-recipe/">turkey tacos</a></strong>, or <a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/mexican-chicken-casserole/"><strong>Mexican chicken casserole</strong></a>, this one deserves a spot in your regular rotation.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-67270 size-full" title="This one pot burrito bowl brings the deliciously authentic flavor you’d expect to find in your favorite Mexican restaurant right to your own table! #onepotmeals #burritobowl" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20735%201102'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Scooping One Pot Burrito Bowl from a pan" width="735" height="1102" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01.jpg 735w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01-200x300.jpg 200w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px" data-lazy-src="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-67270 size-full" title="This one pot burrito bowl brings the deliciously authentic flavor you’d expect to find in your favorite Mexican restaurant right to your own table! #onepotmeals #burritobowl" src="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01.jpg" alt="Scooping One Pot Burrito Bowl from a pan" width="735" height="1102" srcset="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01.jpg 735w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01-200x300.jpg 200w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-01-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px" /></noscript><br /><br /><div id="savetherecipe"><div id="savetherecipe"><div id="savetherecipe"><script async data-uid="f0f296cf68" src="https://gonnawantseconds.kit.com/f0f296cf68/index.js"></script></div></div></div>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 data-section-id="1bjgnsq" data-start="1385" data-end="1426">AT A GLANCE</h2>
<p data-start="1428" data-end="1549"><strong data-start="1428" data-end="1437">Prep:</strong> 10 minutes<br data-start="1448" data-end="1451" /><strong data-start="1451" data-end="1460">Cook:</strong> 45 minutes<br data-start="1471" data-end="1474" /><strong data-start="1474" data-end="1485">Serves:</strong> 6<br data-start="1487" data-end="1490" /><strong data-start="1490" data-end="1505">Difficulty:</strong> Easy<br data-start="1510" data-end="1513" /><strong data-start="1513" data-end="1525">Texture:</strong> Hearty, saucy, cheesy</p>
<h2 data-section-id="1x95pnk" data-start="1556" data-end="1596">🔥 QUICK ANSWER</h2>
<p data-section-id="30e2l4" data-start="1598" data-end="1624"><strong>What Is a Burrito Bowl?</strong></p>
<p data-start="1626" data-end="1779">A burrito bowl is everything you’d normally find in a burrito—rice, seasoned meat, beans, and toppings—served in a bowl instead of wrapped in a tortilla, making it an easy, customizable dinner.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="t5wi26" data-start="953" data-end="991">How to Build a Classic Burrito Bowl</h2>
<p data-start="993" data-end="1092">Traditional burrito bowls are built in layers, similar to what you’d get at Chipotle Mexican Grill:</p>
<ul data-start="1094" data-end="1179">
<li data-section-id="cdifh6" data-start="1094" data-end="1108">Base: rice</li>
<li data-section-id="1xyjoxh" data-start="1109" data-end="1146">Protein: beef, chicken, or turkey</li>
<li data-section-id="xowplf" data-start="1147" data-end="1156">Beans</li>
<li data-section-id="1jgbh34" data-start="1157" data-end="1169">Toppings</li>
<li data-section-id="1sjnqax" data-start="1170" data-end="1179">Sauce</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1181" data-end="1286">This method gives you full control over flavor and texture—but it also means cooking multiple components.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="s46nza" data-start="1697" data-end="1730">An Easier One-Pan Burrito Bowl</h2>
<p data-start="1732" data-end="1854"><strong>This recipe takes those same classic ingredients and simplifies the process by cooking everything together in one skillet.</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1856" data-end="2010">
<li data-section-id="y0w7e7" data-start="1856" data-end="1901">The rice cooks directly in seasoned broth</li>
<li data-section-id="11dkz4e" data-start="1902" data-end="1956">The meat simmers with the spices for deeper flavor</li>
<li data-section-id="sp5im9" data-start="1957" data-end="2010">Beans, corn, and tomatoes add texture and balance</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2012" data-end="2077">The result is a hearty, flavor-packed dinner with minimal effort.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-67272 size-full" title="This one pot burrito bowl brings the deliciously authentic flavor you’d expect to find in your favorite Mexican restaurant right to your own table! #onepotmeals #burritobowl" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20735%201102'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="One Pot Burrito Bowl topped with chopped avocados and tomatoes" width="735" height="1102" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03.jpg 735w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03-200x300.jpg 200w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px" data-lazy-src="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-67272 size-full" title="This one pot burrito bowl brings the deliciously authentic flavor you’d expect to find in your favorite Mexican restaurant right to your own table! #onepotmeals #burritobowl" src="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03.jpg" alt="One Pot Burrito Bowl topped with chopped avocados and tomatoes" width="735" height="1102" srcset="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03.jpg 735w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03-200x300.jpg 200w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/One-Pot-Burrito-Bowl-03-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px" /></noscript></p>
<h2 data-section-id="1b7v96p" data-start="2084" data-end="2118">One-Pan vs Classic Burrito Bowl</h2>
<ul data-start="2120" data-end="2238">
<li data-section-id="8yzf8j" data-start="2120" data-end="2180"><strong data-start="2122" data-end="2142">One-pan version:</strong> Faster, deeper flavor, less cleanup</li>
<li data-section-id="1y9fzhe" data-start="2181" data-end="2238"><strong data-start="2183" data-end="2203">Classic version:</strong> More texture, more customization</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2240" data-end="2305">Both are great—it just depends on what kind of meal you’re after.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="1jas968" data-start="2312" data-end="2333">✨ Before You Begin</h2>
<p data-start="2335" data-end="2427">✨ <strong data-start="2337" data-end="2366">Use long grain white rice: </strong>It holds its shape and cooks evenly without getting mushy.</p>
<p data-start="2429" data-end="2517">✨ <strong data-start="2431" data-end="2452">Toast your spices: </strong>Cooking spices with the onion and garlic builds deeper flavor.</p>
<p data-start="2519" data-end="2602">✨ <strong data-start="2521" data-end="2542">Watch your liquid: </strong>Too much liquid can make the rice soft—measure carefully.</p>
<p data-start="2604" data-end="2687">✨ <strong data-start="2606" data-end="2633">Don’t overcook the meat: </strong>It will finish cooking as it simmers with the rice.</p>
<div class="relative basis-auto flex-col -mb-(--composer-overlap-px) pb-(--composer-overlap-px) [--composer-overlap-px:28px] grow flex">
<div class="flex flex-col text-sm">
<div class="" data-turn-id-container="request-WEB:fe510fda-a0ba-47fd-8063-48fdd41e4958-16" data-is-intersecting="true">
<section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto R6Vx5W_threadScrollVars scroll-mb-[calc(var(--scroll-root-safe-area-inset-bottom,0px)+var(--thread-response-height))] scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="request-WEB:fe510fda-a0ba-47fd-8063-48fdd41e4958-16" data-testid="conversation-turn-34" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant">
