<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">
<h2 data-section-id="cb68ng" data-start="2694" data-end="2720">One Pan Burrito Bowl Ingredients + Key Notes</h2>
<p data-start="2722" data-end="2859">This is just a quick glance at what you’ll need. For exact measurements and the full ingredient list, head down to the recipe card below.</p>
<p><strong data-start="2863" data-end="2888">Ground beef or turkey</strong> – Beef is richer; turkey is leaner</p>
<p><strong data-start="2928" data-end="2953">Long grain white rice</strong> – Best for one-pan texture</p>
<p><strong data-start="2985" data-end="3000">Black beans</strong> – Classic burrito bowl staple</p>
<p><strong data-start="3035" data-end="3068">Diced tomatoes + green chiles</strong> – Flavor + moisture</p>
<p><strong data-start="3093" data-end="3127">Chicken stock (caldo de pollo)</strong> – Adds depth</p>
<p><strong data-start="3145" data-end="3153">Corn</strong> – Sweetness and texture</p>
<p><strong data-start="3182" data-end="3209">Cheddar + Monterey Jack</strong> – Melty, flavorful finish</p>
<h2 data-section-id="6dq60h" data-start="3244" data-end="3261">🥣 How to Make</h2>
<p data-start="3263" data-end="3368"><strong data-start="3263" data-end="3282">Brown the meat. </strong>Cook the ground beef or turkey with salt and pepper until just cooked, then remove.</p>
<p data-start="3370" data-end="3439"><strong data-start="3370" data-end="3390">Sauté aromatics. </strong>Cook onion and garlic until soft and fragrant.</p>
<p data-start="3441" data-end="3528"><strong data-start="3441" data-end="3462">Bloom the spices. </strong>Add chili powder, cumin, oregano, and paprika and cook briefly.</p>
<p data-start="3530" data-end="3625"><strong data-start="3530" data-end="3554">Add everything else. </strong>Stir in rice, tomatoes, beans, chiles, corn, broth, and cooked meat.</p>
<p data-start="3627" data-end="3694"><strong data-start="3627" data-end="3638">Simmer. </strong>Cover and cook until rice is tender and fully cooked.</p>
<p data-start="3696" data-end="3774"><strong data-start="3696" data-end="3719">Finish with cheese. </strong>Top with cheese, cover, and let melt before serving.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="deef6w" data-start="3781" data-end="3802">🔬 Cooking Science</h2>
<p data-start="3804" data-end="3975">Rice absorbs liquid as it cooks, pulling in the broth, spices, and meat juices. That’s why one-pan versions develop such rich, cohesive flavor compared to assembled bowls.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="1p791x2" data-start="3982" data-end="4012">⚠️ Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
<ul data-start="4014" data-end="4181">
<li data-section-id="ofc77b" data-start="4014" data-end="4053">Adding too much liquid → mushy rice</li>
<li data-section-id="1m4p3z9" data-start="4054" data-end="4095">Skipping spice toasting → flat flavor</li>
<li data-section-id="7kzwbs" data-start="4096" data-end="4134">Overcooking the meat → dry texture</li>
<li data-section-id="1rcb4zg" data-start="4135" data-end="4181">Lifting the lid too often → uneven cooking</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-section-id="1sg7j1i" data-start="4188" data-end="4201">⭐ Pro Tips</h2>
<p data-start="4203" data-end="4343">⭐ Add lime juice at the end for brightness</p>
<p data-start="4203" data-end="4343">⭐ Use freshly shredded cheese for best melt</p>
<p data-start="4203" data-end="4343">⭐ Add toppings right before serving for texture</p>
<h2 data-section-id="zjpx41" data-start="4350" data-end="4402">Storing + Reheating + Freezing + Make-Ahead Tips</h2>
<h3 data-section-id="w9wz4s" data-start="4404" data-end="4415">Storing</h3>
<p data-start="4416" data-end="4538">Store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 4 days. The flavors continue to develop as it sits.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="ae9289" data-start="4540" data-end="4553">Reheating</h3>
<p data-start="4554" data-end="4727">For larger portions, cover the dish with foil and reheat in a 350°F oven for 15–20 minutes. If reheating from a glass or ceramic dish, let it come to room temperature first.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="1y6g688" data-start="4729" data-end="4741">Freezing</h3>
<p data-start="4742" data-end="4845">Freeze in portioned containers for up to 2 months. Thaw overnight in the refrigerator before reheating.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="864uyo" data-start="4847" data-end="4861">Make-Ahead</h3>
<p data-start="4862" data-end="4962">You can make this ahead and reheat, or prep toppings separately and assemble fresh for best texture.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="145p14x" data-start="278" data-end="299">What to Serve With</h2>
<h3 data-section-id="99ems" data-start="301" data-end="324">Fresh + Crisp Sides</h3>
<ul data-start="326" data-end="527">
<li><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/1905-salad/"><strong>1905 Salad</strong></a> – crisp, zesty, and bold, with just enough bite to balance the richness</li>
<li data-section-id="1xc5xgo" data-start="326" data-end="440"></li>
<li data-section-id="1xc5xgo" data-start="326" data-end="440"><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/pineapple-coleslaw/"><strong>Pineapple Coleslaw</strong> </a>– sweet, tangy, and crunchy with a tropical twist that pairs perfectly with Tex-Mex flavors</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="xeep28" data-start="534" data-end="554">Comforting Sides</h3>
<ul data-start="556" data-end="718">
<li><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/mexican-cornbread/"><strong>Mexican Cornbread</strong></a> – warm, slightly sweet, and perfect for soaking up all those bold flavors</li>
<li><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/drunken-mexican-beans-with-cilantro-and-bacon/"><strong>Charro Beans</strong> </a>– smoky, savory, and packed with flavor that complements the bowl beautifully</li>
<li data-section-id="pecmh4" data-start="556" data-end="623"><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/mexican-rice/"><strong>Mexican Rice</strong></a> – classic, flavorful, and always a natural pairing</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="12z5kr7" data-start="725" data-end="743">Sweet Finishes</h3>
<ul data-start="745" data-end="997">
<li><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/frescas-con-crema/"><strong>Fresas con Crema</strong></a> – fresh strawberries in a sweet, creamy sauce for a light, refreshing finish</li>
<li data-section-id="1w7womp" data-start="745" data-end="832"><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/no-bake-pineapple-pie/"><strong>No Bake Pineapple Pie</strong></a> – cool, creamy, and lightly sweet with bright tropical flavor</li>
<li data-section-id="n0vizn" data-start="931" data-end="997"><a href="https://www.gonnawantseconds.com/fudge-pie/"><strong>Fudge Pie</strong></a> – rich, chocolatey, and the perfect indulgent ending</li>
</ul>
